HEADWORD: Opsiometer
<hw>Op`si*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ sight
+ <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F. <ets>opsiom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for measuring the limits of distinct vision in different
individuals, and thus determining the proper focal length of a lens for
correcting imperfect sight.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

